SIMPLE: uncertain
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncertain
<hw>Un*cer"tain</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*s⟦etil⟧r"t⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>certain</ets>. Cf.
<er>Incertain</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not certain; not having
certain knowledge; not assured in mind; distrustful.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Man, without the protection of a superior Being, . . . is
<qex>uncertain</qex> of everything that he hopes for.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Irresolute; inconsonant; variable; untrustworthy;
<as>as, an <ex>uncertain</ex> person; an <ex>uncertain</ex>
breeze</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O woman! in our hours of ease,⟦br⟧
<qex>Uncertain</qex>, coy, and hard to please!</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Questionable; equivocal; indefinite;
problematical.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The fashion of <xex>uncertain</xex>
evils.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From certain dangers to <qex>uncertain</qex> praise.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not sure; liable to fall or err; fallible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soon bent his bow, <qex>uncertain</qex> in his aim.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whistling slings dismissed the <qex>uncertain</qex> stone.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Precarious</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncertain</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncertain
<hw>Un*cer"tain</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> +
<ets>certain</ets>; or fr. <ets>uncertain</ets>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To make uncertain.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W.
Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncertainly</ent>⟦br⟧
